@startuml NeuroScreen-A Deployment Diagram
!define AWSPUML https://raw.githubusercontent.com/awslabs/aws-icons-for-plantuml/v14.0/dist
!include AWSPUML/AWSCommon.puml

title NeuroScreen-A: Diagrama de Despliegue\nArquitectura de Microservicios con Docker

' Definición de dispositivos
artifact "📱 Cliente" as CLIENT {
  artifact "Navegador Web" as BROWSER {
    artifact "React SPA" as REACT_APP
  }
}

artifact "🖥️ Docker Host" as DOCKER_HOST {
  
  ' Red Frontend
  artifact "frontend_net" as FRONTEND_NET {
    component "**Frontend Container**\n[Port: 9002:8080]" as FRONTEND_CONTAINER {
      artifact "Nginx Server" as NGINX
      artifact "React Build\n(node_modules,\nbuild artifacts)" as REACT_BUILD
    }
  }

  ' Red Backend
  artifact "backend_net" as BACKEND_NET {
    
    component "**API Container**\n[Port: 5000]" as API_CONTAINER {
      artifact "Flask Application\n(Gunicorn)" as FLASK_APP
      artifact "@app/routes\n@app/services\n@app/models" as FLASK_MODULES
      database "@app/ml/\nEEG Models\nPreprocessing" as ML_MODELS
      artifact "Security & Auth\n(JWT, CORS, Rate Limiting)" as FLASK_SECURITY
    }

    component "**Worker Container**\n[Celery]" as WORKER_CONTAINER {
      artifact "Celery Worker" as CELERY_WORKER
      artifact "@app/tasks/\neeg_tasks.py" as CELERY_TASKS
      artifact "EEG Inference\n& Processing" as CELERY_PROCESSING
    }

    component "**Database**\n[PostgreSQL 15]" as DB_CONTAINER {
      database "postgres_data\nvolume" as POSTGRES_DB
      artifact "Alembic Migrations\nv1: Initial Schema" as DB_MIGRATIONS
      artifact "SQLAlchemy Models:\n- User\n- Patient\n- EEG Records\n- Predictions" as DB_MODELS
    }

    component "**Cache**\n[Redis 7]" as REDIS_CONTAINER {
      database "redis_data\nvolume" as REDIS_STORE
      artifact "Session Storage\nCelery Queue" as REDIS_FUNCTIONS
    }

    component "**Shared Storage**" as STORAGE {
      database "eeg_uploads\nvolume" as UPLOADS_VOLUME
      database "DL Models\nvolume (ro)" as MODELS_VOLUME
      artifact "eegnet_model.keras" as EEGNET_MODEL
      artifact "Preprocessed\nEEG files" as EEG_FILES
    }
  }
}


' === RELACIONES HTTP/REST ===
CLIENT -->|GET / POST\nHTTP/HTTPS\nJSON| BROWSER
BROWSER -->|Port 9002\nHTTP Requests\n(Vite dev/prod)| FRONTEND_CONTAINER
FRONTEND_CONTAINER -->|GET /api/*\nJWT Token\nJSON| API_CONTAINER

' === RELACIONES ENTRE CONTENEDORES BACKEND ===
API_CONTAINER -->|Send Task\n(celery.send_task)| CELERY_WORKER : Redis Broker
CELERY_WORKER -->|Retrieve Task\nfrom Queue| REDIS_CONTAINER : REDIS_URL

API_CONTAINER -->|CRUD Operations\n(SQLAlchemy)| DB_CONTAINER : TCP 5432
CELERY_WORKER -->|Read/Write\nEEG Results| DB_CONTAINER : TCP 5432

API_CONTAINER -->|Cache Auth/Session\n(redis-py)| REDIS_CONTAINER : TCP 6379
CELERY_WORKER -->|Store Results\nUpdate Progress| REDIS_CONTAINER : TCP 6379

' === RELACIONES DE ALMACENAMIENTO ===
FLASK_APP -->|Load Models\n(Keras)| MODELS_VOLUME "/app/dl_models:ro"
CELERY_PROCESSING -->|Load & Execute\nEEG Inference| EEGNET_MODEL
CELERY_PROCESSING -->|Write Predictions| UPLOADS_VOLUME "/app/uploads"
API_CONTAINER -->|Read/Serve\nEEG Records| UPLOADS_VOLUME "/app/uploads"

' === RELACIONES INTERNAS DE CONTENEDORES ===
API_CONTAINER -->|Gunicorn Workers\n(1.5 CPU, 1GB RAM)| FLASK_MODULES
FLASK_MODULES -->|Import| ML_MODELS
FLASK_MODULES -->|Enforce| FLASK_SECURITY

CELERY_WORKER -->|Export\ncelery instance| CELERY_TASKS
CELERY_TASKS -->|Inference Pipeline| CELERY_PROCESSING

DB_CONTAINER -->|Init Schema| DB_MODELS
DB_CONTAINER -->|Versioning| DB_MIGRATIONS

' === CONFIGURACIÓN Y HEALTHCHECKS ===
API_CONTAINER -.->|Depends on\n(service_healthy)| DB_CONTAINER : Healthcheck: pg_isready
WORKER_CONTAINER -.->|Depends on\n(service_healthy)| DB_CONTAINER
API_CONTAINER -.->|Depends on\n(service_healthy)| REDIS_CONTAINER : Healthcheck: redis-cli ping
WORKER_CONTAINER -.->|Depends on\n(service_healthy)| REDIS_CONTAINER
FRONTEND_CONTAINER -.->|Depends on| API_CONTAINER : docker-compose

' === VOLÚMENES Y RED DECLARADOS ===
note right of BACKEND_NET
  **Redes Privadas Docker:**
  - frontend_net: Frontend ↔ API
  - backend_net: API ↔ Worker ↔ DB ↔ Redis
  
  **Aislamiento de Red:**
  - Cap_drop: ALL
  - Cap_add: CHOWN, SETUID, SETGID
  - no-new-privileges: true
end note

note bottom of DOCKER_HOST
  **Volumenes Persistentes:**
  - postgres_data: BD PostgreSQL
  - redis_data: Cache/Queue
  - eeg_uploads: Registros EEG + Predicciones
  - dl_models: Modelos ML (read-only)
  
  **Límites de Recursos:**
  - API: 1.5 CPU, 1GB RAM
  - Worker: 1 CPU, 2GB RAM
  - Frontend: 0.5 CPU, 256MB RAM
  - Redis: 256MB RAM
end note

note left of CLIENT
  **Flujo de Datos del Usuario:**
  1. Cliente accede http://localhost:9002
  2. Nginx sirve React SPA
  3. Frontend realiza GET /api/health
  4. Frontend autentica: POST /api/auth/login
  5. Frontend obtiene: GET /api/patients
  6. Cliente carga EEG: POST /api/eeg_records
  7. Celery procesa asincronamente
  8. Cliente consulta: GET /api/predictions
end note

@enduml
